data.enText: to make sb move quickly by pushing them in a rough aggressive way

data.chText: 他抓住她的胳膊把她推出房间。
data.enText: He grabbed her arm and hustled her out of the room.
to force sb to make a decision before they are ready or sure
to sell or obtain sth, often illegally
They survive by hustling on the streets.
to act in an aggressive way or with a lot of energy
busy noisy activity of a lot of people in one place

data.chText: 我们周末时躲开了城市的拥挤喧嚣。
data.enText: We escaped from the hustle and bustle of the city for the weekend.

ex.chText: 她匆匆回家告诉我们这一消息。
ex.enText: She hurried home to tell us the news.

ex.chText: 他们匆忙地去赶公共汽车。
ex.enText: They hurried to catch their bus.

synonyms.bx: 指因时间不充裕而匆促行事。

ex.chText: 她总是在家里忙得团团转。
ex.enText: She is always bustling round the house.

ex.chText: 他看着人们匆匆地进出超级市场。
ex.enText: He watched people bustle in and out of the supermarket.

synonyms.bx: 指要做的事情很多，有时还伴有闹哄哄的氛围。

ex.chText: 要想赶上这趟航班的话，你得抓紧时间。
ex.enText: You have to hustle if you want to make this flight.

ex.chText: 要是我们动作快些，可以准时到那儿。
ex.enText: We can get there in time if we hustle.

synonyms.bx: 指匆忙去某处或做某事。

tr: a swindle in which you cheat at gambling or persuade a person to buy worthless property
pressure or urge someone into an action
move or cause to move energetically or busily
example: The cheerleaders bustled about excitingly before their performance

tr: cause to move furtively and hurriedly
example: The secret service agents hustled the speaker out of the amphitheater
she hustled a free lunch from the waiter

tr: sell something to or obtain something from by energetic and especially underhanded activity

value.def: If you hustle someone, you try to make them go somewhere or do something quickly, for example by pulling or pushing them along.

example.ex: The guards hustled Harry out of the car...
example.tran: 卫兵将哈里从车里拉了出来。

example.ex: There was no opportunity to ask anything more as the guards hustled us away.
example.tran: 卫兵把我们推搡走了，我们没有机会再多问。

value.def: If you hustle, you go somewhere or do something as quickly as you can.

example.ex: You'll have to hustle if you're to get home for supper...
example.tran: 你想赶回家吃晚饭的话，就得加快速度。

example.ex: He hustled straight up the aircraft steps without looking round or waving goodbye...
example.tran: 他急匆匆地径直登上飞机舷梯，没有环顾四周，也没有挥手告别。

example.ex: They had finished the exam and the teacher was hustling to get the papers gathered up.
example.tran: 他们已经考完试了，老师正在赶紧收卷子。

value.def: If someone hustles, they try to earn money or gain an advantage from a situation, often by using dishonest or illegal means.

example.ex: We're expected to hustle and fight for what we want...
example.tran: 我们应该为得到自己想要的而不择手段，奋力争取。

example.ex: I hustled some tickets from a magazine and off we went.
example.tran: 我从一家杂志社骗了几张票，然后我们就一起去了。

value.tran: （常指用不正当或非法的手段）谋取;骗钱;诈取

example.ex: Shell Cottage provides the perfect retreat from the hustle and bustle of London...
example.tran: 谢尔农舍为想要躲避伦敦的忙碌喧嚣的人们提供了一个绝佳的休闲之所。

example.ex: She waited until they were beyond the hustle of the Washington Saturday night traffic.
example.tran: 她一直等到他们远离了华盛顿周六晚上的车水马龙。
